AFTER:
Extract a shared validateTransportConfig(config) function in a common location (e.g., types.ts or a new validation.ts). Call it from both store.add() and createTransport(). The transport-factory guards can remain as defensive checks, but with an explicit comment: '// Defensive: validated at store level'.

WHY: Single source of truth for transport validation rules. Currently, adding a new transport type (e.g., 'grpc') requires updating validation in two files. A shared validator reduces the risk of divergence.

